22/08/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Rotation of the fifth and sixth Croatian contingents deployed in Afghanistan as part of the International Security Force begins this week, according to Croatia's National Co-ordinator for NATO, Pjer Simunovic. 
On Friday (19 August), he announced that Zagreb would send a new unit of 50 military policemen to Afghanistan for a six-month deployment. 
After that, Croatia would increase the number of its personnel in Afghanistan to 150, a move recently endorsed by the Croatian Parliament. 
Also this week, the four Croatian members of a joint medical team manned by personnel from Albania and Macedonia would join their colleagues in Kabul. 
(Vjesnik, Novi list - 20/08/05)
